<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 5000 9100 9200 9400 9900 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 5000, 5000i, 9000, 9000i - TROUBLESHOOTING - SPEEDOMETER SENSOR AND CIRCUITS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SPEEDOMETER SENSOR AND CIRCUITS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08207x_10.xml" xrefid="x0820705">SPEEDOMETER</hotlnk>
                for operation description of speedometer circuits.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x082075a">
            <title>Inspecting And Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect engine harness connector from the sensor. Loosen the locknut and remove the
                    sensor. The harness connector and sensor should be free of damage or corrosion. Remove any metal
                    shavings or debris from the sensor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the sensor, turn in until the sensor contacts the transmission speedometer
                    gear, then back out
                    <emph type="bold">one full turn.</emph>
                    Tighten lock nut to 15 ft-lbs. (20.3 N&#183; m). This assures that the sensor is adjusted properly
                    for the next test.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>To perform this test, construct two test leads using terminals (P/N 1680205C1) and suitable length of
                16GA wire. Install terminals on one end and alligator clips on the other.
            </para>
            <table id="t0820710" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing the VSS</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.48in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.67in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With VSS disconnected, use test lead to measure resistance to ground at both
                                    <emph type="bold">sensor</emph>
                                    terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Sensor terminals to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the VSS (refer to paragraphs above).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Use test leads and measure resistance between VSS sensor terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Between sensor terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>600 to 900 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the VSS (refer to paragraphs above).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Perform sensor output test below.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>2.0 AC volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>VSS checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the VSS (refer to paragraphs above).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>VSS Sensor Output Test</title>
            </para>
            <para>This test checks for proper AC voltage output from the VSS sensor. Improper adjustment will cause LOW,
                ERRATIC, or NO sensor output.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury, put blocks under the front tires to stop the vehicle from moving.
                        Always use safety stands to support the vehicle.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>EXTREME CAUTION should be used to prevent personal injury resulting from contact with rotating
                        vehicle wheels when connecting test leads.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Block front wheels and place rear axles on floor stands.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Use AC voltmeter with sufficient length leads to avoid personal contact with rotating vehicle
                        wheels during this test. Connect meter leads to test leads.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Run engine at idle speed, with transmission in high gear. Measure voltage across the two
                        sensor terminals.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Sensor output should be 2.0 AC volts or more.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Signal To Speedometer/Tachometer Module (Mechanical Engine Only)</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To test Vehicle Speed Sensor circuits to the ECM with electronic engines, refer to Group 08 -
                        Electronic Engine Controls in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Perform
                <hotlnk xrefid="x082075a">Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor</hotlnk>
                before performing this test!
            </para>
            <table id="t0820711" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Signal To Speedometer/Tachometer Module (Mechanical Engine Only)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.74in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.63in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Remove conn. (421) from Speedometer/ Tachometer module and disconnect engine
                                    harness connector (88) from the vehicle speed sensor. At conn. (421) measure
                                    resistance to ground at circuits 47A and 47B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(421), 47A and 47B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit with less than 100K resistance, between
                                    connectors (421) and (88), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (421) measure resistance between circuits 47A and 47B and between all
                                    other circuits in the connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(421), 47A and 47B and all other circuits.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short between any circuits with less than 100K resistance between
                                    terminals, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (88) use test lead to jumper circuit 47A to ground. At conn. (421)
                                    measure resistance to ground at cir. 47A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(421), 47A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 47A between connectors (421) to (88), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (88) use test lead to jumper circuit 47B to ground. At connector
                                    (421) measure resistance to ground at circuit 47B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(421), 47B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 47B between connectors (88) and (421), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>The vehicle speed sensor and connecting circuits check good. If speedometer and
                                    tachometer gauges were switched (see
                                    <hotlnk document="s08207x_40.xml" xrefid="x0820708">GAUGE CIRCUIT
                                        TROUBLESHOOTING</hotlnk>) then replace the Speedometer/Tachometer module.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
